Forms (Part 3): <label>, <textarea>, <select>

Example Code:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Day 17: Form Elements Part 3</title>
</head>
<body>

  <h1>Day 17: Label, Textarea, Select</h1>

  <form action="/submit" method="post">

    <label for="bio">Your Bio:</label><br>
    <textarea id="bio" name="bio" rows="5" cols="40" placeholder="Write something about yourself..."></textarea><br><br>

    <label for="country">Choose your country:</label><br>
    <select id="country" name="country">
      <option value="india">India</option>
      <option value="usa">USA</option>
      <option value="uk">UK</option>
      <option value="canada">Canada</option>
    </select><br><br>

    <input type="submit" value="Submit">

  </form>

</body>
</html>

Explanation:
--<label for="id">: Connects a label to an input element using the id.
--<textarea>: Lets users enter multiple lines of text.
--<select>: Creates a dropdown menu.
--<option>: Defines choices inside the dropdown.


